synopses.synopsis: The exact same show as Fibber McGee and Molly, only 'Molly' (Marian Jordan) was missing during this time. She was gone so long with an ailment (either a nervous breakdown or alcoholism, or both) that the name of the program was changed during her absence.

The story of Jim and Marian Jordan has probably been told and retold more than any other tale of the microphone: how two ordinary people from the heartland, through tenacity and hard work, climbed to the heights and showed Hollywood insiders how radio should be done. - On the Air: The Encyclopedia of Old-Time Radio by John Dunning
